@node "Changes" "Changes to MegaRXDL"


CHANGES

MegaRXDL now only needs two arguments on the command line... eg:
   MegaRXDL <XCBD> <FILE to store download paths/files>

   MegaRXDL ~20 MRXDL~14.sfl

  22-July-95 2.05 It will also work correctly after a goodbye
                  after download.

@endnode

@node "Intro" "MegaRXDL Introduction"


Introduction

MegaRXDL is a Shareware Download Interface Program for Xenolink 1.95 +. It
allows users to download files from Xenolink as normal downloads or if a @{"text" link "extfile" 0}
@{"file defined" link "extfile" 0} in the @{"command line" link "Install" 0} exists, it will add the contained filepaths
and files to the users download list, and continue with a normal system
download.. This makes it a very handy util for external programs written in
Arexx, which are unable to carry out direct downloading without attaching to
messages via Junkmail ©.. It is part of my Shareware CD-Rom door program for
Xenolink, but released also as a separate door for those who want to interface
it with existing programs that are unable to do direct downloading..

NOTE: Upon @{"registering" link "rego" 0} MegaRXDL you will obtain a keyfile that will enable the
full functions of this program, to use as you wish on your system.

You may also @{"register" link "rego" 0} this program on it's own to use with other software..


@endnode

