@node "Install" "MegaRXDL Installation"


Installation

1:     Place MegaRXDL in a directory called
       MegaRXDl inside
       your Doors: assign..

       eg. Doors:MegaRXDL/MegaRXDL

2:     Place your keyfile in this directory also. @{"(if you registered)" link "rego" 0}

       eg. Doors:MegaRXDL/keyfile

3:     Edit your menu.src file you wish to run MegaRXDL from..

       eg.
       CMD = "D"
           {
       XenolinkDoor "^20000^2^Doors:MegaRXDL/MegaRXDL ~20 T:MRXDL~14.sfl"
            }

       The syntax of the command for MegaRXDL is as follows:
       MegaRXDL <XCBD> @{"<File listing names to download>" link "extfile" 0}

       I add the extra@{" ~14 in the filename in T: " link "extfile" 0}so as to keep multiple
       lists created on different nodes from overwriting each other.
       I have tested it only slightly on two nodes at the same time..
       It may work on more, but I only have one line..

4:     Please NOTE that MegaRXDL CAN COMPLETLY replace your normal Xenolink
       download function BatchDownload..  If the @{"file specified" link "extfile" 0} in the
       commandline is not found, it will simply continue to download
       any files already marked on the system found in the Filecat.
       It will not remove any files already marked on the system as it is
       started..
       It does not interfere with the normal file/byte ratios..

5:     Recompile the menu source you added the command to..

6:     Try it out..  NOTE: In the unregistered form, MegaRXDL will continue
       to work with only two setbacks..
       (a) It will cause a delay after it finds there is no keyfile..
       (b) It will only read in a few external files from the specified
       text file containing the path and names of files to add to the
       system download list..

NOTE:  It will however send ALL marked files that are marked normall
       from Xenolink's filecat.
 

@endnode

@node "extfile" "The External file"


Description of the External File


The file that is read by MegaRXDL can be anywhere on your system, although
placing it in RAM: or T: is a good idea to reduce disk access..

The file must be a standard ascii text file containing the FULL path to the
directory in which the file to be download is situated, and of course, the
name of the file to send..

The format of the file:

Full Path including the trailing / or :<space or tab>then the full filename.

CD0:Aminet/biz/dbase/ Filename.lha Aminet5:comms/bbs/ Nextfile.lha DH3:
Anotherfile.lha

It is recommended that you keep to just the one space or tab between the path
and the filename..
 

@endnode

@node "rego" "Registration"


REGISTRATION

MegaRXDL is NOT a free program. It is released under the Shareware principle.
This means you get to test it for free, for a MAXIMUM period of 30 days. By
this time your users would have complained enough for you to need professional
help, or you would have deleted it. :) If you like it and wish to continue to
use it beyond this period, you are then requested to please register your
copy. The registration fee is A$30 (Thirty dollars Australian), which is
around US$25.

